Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a garlic press). Roughly chop the @olives{30}(roughly chopped). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved) and roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Place the tomatoes and parsley in a #bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180} to your boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{} and pop back into the #pan{}. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @pine nuts{15}(no oil). Toast them until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}, tossing regularly. When golden, transfer them from your pan to a bowl.

> TIP: Watch the pine nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat and add a drizzle of oil. Add the shallot to your pan, then stir and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @tomato puree{30}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped), olives and @vegetable stock paste{10}. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by half, ~{10%minutes}.

While your sauce cooks, finely chop the @chives{1}. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pull it apart into small pieces. Stir the @balsamic vinegar{12}, @honey{15} and @olive oil{1}(for the dressing) into the bowl of tomatoes.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When your sauce is cooked, season to taste with salt and pepper, then add the drained pasta and toss together. Stir through half the chives and half the mozzarella then share into #bowls{}. Spoon your tomato salsa on top along with the remaining mozzarella, chives and a sprinkle of pine nuts. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 4: If you've chosen to add diced chicken breast to your meal, add it to the pan
> when you add the shallot and cook for the same amount of time as the shallot. Continue
> with the recipe as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and
> its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> Add @?diced chicken breast{260} when adding the shallot if using.